# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-36
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Algebraic manipulation"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In algebraic manipulation, pupils use apply knowledge of the distributive law to find the product of two binomaials in order to factorise quadratics."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is the foundation for a lot of the generalisation done in this year, and is placed at the start of the year accordingly.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Collect like terms and use basic algebra
Expand and factorise expressions
Substitute values into algebraic formulas""" ;
  curric:id "36"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.339087Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-39
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Arithmetic procedures: index laws"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils learn how to manipulate indices and perform calculations without conversion by understanding index laws."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on the index work covered in the previous unit to formalise laws around indices.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand and apply powers and roots
Use rules for multiplying and dividing powers
Apply zero, negative and fractional indices""" ;
  curric:id "39"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.440421Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-40
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Standard form calculations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to add, subtract, multiply and divide numbers written in standard form."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow "This unit deepens pupil understanding of index laws to now cover standard form." ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand powers of 10 and place value
Convert numbers to and from standard form
Perform calculations using multiplication/division of powers of 10""" ;
  curric:id "40"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.498942Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-38
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Percentages"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to perform simple and compound interest calculations using percentages."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from percentage change and because it utilises a formula it follows on from more work on algebra.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Convert between fractions, decimals, and percentages
Find percentages of amounts (including 50%, 25%, 10%)
Use percentage increase/decrease in context""" ;
  curric:id "38"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.542331Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-51
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Angles"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils use their knowledge of corresponding, alternate and co-interior angles to reason through and solve more complicated problems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds upon the preceding unit on shape and develops fluency of understanding of angles.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify types of angles (acute, obtuse, right, reflex)
Understand angle facts (e.g. angles on a line, around a point)
Use a protractor to measure and draw angles""" ;
  curric:id "51"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.574743Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-52
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Further transformations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils apply their knowledge of transformations to explore negative enlargement factors and the application of multiple transformations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit extends knowledge of transformations with combinations of transformations. It purposefully follows extended work on ratios as this is a key skill in this unit.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify translations, reflections and rotations
Use vector notation for translations
Describe transformations using appropriate language and coordinates""" ;
  curric:id "52"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.575303Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-49
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "2D and 3D shape: compound shapes"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, knowledge of circles and polygons is drawn upon to find the arc length and area of a circle sector and areas of complex compound shapes."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is a summation of KS3 work on shape, but extends into parts of a circle and more complicated compound shapes.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify and name standard 2D and 3D shapes
Calculate area, perimeter, and volume of standard shapes
Break down complex shapes into known components""" ;
  curric:id "49"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.588883Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-41
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sampling"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to sample, and explore accuracy and limitations with various sampling strategies and data collection techniques."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This topic is placed here to benefit from interleaving and builds from prior learning around numerical summaries of data.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand the concept of a population and sample
Recognise bias and representativeness
Select and justify methods of sampling""" ;
  curric:id "41"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.589429Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-statistics .

oakcurric:unit-69
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Vectors"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupil understanding of vectors is deepened with pupils exploring column vector notation and arithmetic procedures."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit requires confidence in different notation and types of notation as well as strong geometric reasoning and number skills. As such it is placed here as units covering those skills have been completed.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand direction and magnitude
Add and subtract vectors using diagrams or components
Represent vectors algebraically in 2D""" ;
  curric:id "69"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.590674Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-68
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Similarity"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils investigate the effect of an enlargement on the perimeter and area of a 2-D shape and the volume of a 3-D shape."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow "This unit builds upon work completed on shape, ratio and transformations." ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise congruent shapes
Understand scale factors and enlargement
Use ratio to compare lengths, areas or volumes""" ;
  curric:id "68"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.591296Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-47
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Linear graphs"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils consider equations that produce parallel or perpendicular graphs and how their equations relate to each other."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit requires strong algebraic skills and understanding of proof, as well as building upon prior knowledge on ratio to work with line segments.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Plot coordinates in all four quadrants
Understand gradient and y-intercept in y = mx + c
Interpret real-life contexts with linear graphs""" ;
  curric:id "47"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.591881Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra ,
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-44
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Graphical representations of data: cumulative frequency and histograms"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils consider cumulative frequency graphs and histograms, and compare these with other known graphical representations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues work on representing and interpreting data and incorporates knowledge developed in Year 10 on comparisons of data. Here we also develop the use of technology to better understand and interrogate data.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Interpret grouped data tables
Plot and interpret frequency and cumulative frequency graphs
Understand class intervals and scale in histograms""" ;
  curric:id "44"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.592427Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-statistics .

oakcurric:unit-50
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "2D and 3D shape: surface area and volume (pyramids, spheres and cones)"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will further develop their understanding of shapes by considering the surface area and volume of pyramids, spheres and cones."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues work on area and volume from the Year 10, introducing more complicated shapes including pyramids, spheres and cones.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify and name 2D and 3D shapes
Recall and use area and volume formulas for simple solids
Apply formulas for curved surfaces and composite shapes""" ;
  curric:id "50"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.593005Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-60
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Conditional probability"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils use their knowledge of calculating theoretical probabilities and extend it to calculate conditional probabilities."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is placed here to assist interleaving, and draws upon prior knowledge from the unit 'Probability: theoretical probabilities' in Year 9 moving into more complex models of probability.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Interpret probability using tables and tree diagrams
Understand dependent vs independent events
Use multiplication and addition rules in probability""" ;
  curric:id "60"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.613178Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-probability .

oakcurric:unit-37
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Simultaneous equations: 2 variables"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn to solve a pair of simultaneous equations from different starting points and cases using a variety of strategies."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from solving equations in Year 8 and develops those skills further.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Solve linear equations in one variable
Interpret solutions graphically
Substitute values into expressions""" ;
  curric:id "37"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.613750Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-67
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Inequalities"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils extend their understanding of inequalities and consider a range of contextual inequalities and ways to find and represent their solutions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit requires strong knowledge of number, manipulation of number, and number generalisation through algebraic skills. Here we further develop that understanding and investigate similar themes through inequalities rather than equations.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Solve linear equations
Represent inequalities on number lines
Interpret inequality symbols and solutions""" ;
  curric:id "67"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.614311Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-71
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Transformations of graphs"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils learn how to perform transformations on functions both algebraically and visually."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit explores the structure of transforming graphs and as such it is positioned after function notation which is essential knowledge building towards this unit.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand horizontal and vertical shifts
Know equations of standard graphs (e.g., y = x_, y = √x)
Interpret effect of operations on graph shape and position""" ;
  curric:id "71"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.616506Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-58
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Right-angled trigonometry"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils are introduced to a variety of situations where trigonometric ratios are required, such as 3-D problems and problems of elevation or depression."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit requires good understanding of ratios, trigonometric ratios and manipulation of formulae, as such it is positoned after several units revisiting and building upon these key skills.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify opposite, adjacent and hypotenuse
Use Pythagoras' Theorem
Understand ratios in similar triangles""" ;
  curric:id "58"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.617077Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-62
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Real-life graphs"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils expand upon knowledge developed in the linear graphs unit. Pupils are introduced to rates of change and the gradient of the tangent as a way of estimating the gradient of a curve."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In the previous unit, pupils looked at compound measures liike speed, and this work is further developed to look at speed distance time graphs, and links features of graphs to practical interpretation.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Interpret linear graphs and trends
Understand units and labels in context (e.g. distance/time)
Use graphs to describe rates and changes""" ;
  curric:id "62"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.617699Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra ,
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-59
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non right-angled trigonometry"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore how to apply knowledge in trigonometry to non right-angled triangles."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues work that pupils completed at the end of Year 10, furthering investigation into trigonometry to incorporate non right-angled triangles.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use the sine, cosine and tangent ratios in right-angled triangles
Apply Pythagoras' Theorem
Interpret the sine and cosine rules for any triangle""" ;
  curric:id "59"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.618276Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra ,
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-42
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Graphical representations of data: scatter graphs and time series"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to interpret and extract data from scatter graphs and time series graphs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from data sampling to deepen understanding of the ways in which data can be interpreted and interrogated.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Plot coordinates in all four quadrants
Interpret trends and patterns in data
Understand correlation and basic statistical language""" ;
  curric:id "42"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.622146Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-statistics .

oakcurric:unit-63
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Direct and inverse proportion"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn how to represent direct and inverse proportion algebraically as an extension of work done in the linear graphs unit."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit we continue work from linear graphs, and link to the previous unit through interpreting graphs which is utilised here when discussing direct and inverse proportion.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand ratios and scaling
Use the unitary method to solve proportional problems
Identify and apply proportional relationships""" ;
  curric:id "63"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.622679Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-57
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Algebraic fractions"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils apply skills in manupulating and solving various equations and formulae to algebraic fractions in order to change the subject and manipulate them."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit we are building on a solid foundation of number and algebra skills to extend into algebraic fractions which require strong skills in algebraic manipulation.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Simplify algebraic expressions
Apply fraction rules to algebraic terms
Factor and cancel common algebraic factors""" ;
  curric:id "57"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.630501Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-48
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-linear graphs"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit graphical representations of non-linear graphs are introduced and explored, and their key features identified."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds upon the preceding unit to incorporate non-linear graphs as well.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Plot and interpret coordinates from equations
Recognise linear and basic quadratic forms
Understand symmetry and turning points""" ;
  curric:id "48"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.633476Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-55
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Bearings"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils apply their knowledge of angles in order to calculate bearings and solve angle problems within the context of bearings."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit requires trigonometry, spatial awareness and angle facts to be able to calculate bearings and reverse bearings. As such it is positioned after those units of work.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Measure angles accurately using a protractor
Use a compass and draw angles from North
Apply knowledge of angles on a straight line and at a point""" ;
  curric:id "55"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.636675Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-61
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Compound measures"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore the multiplicative relationship between different compound meaures and units such as speed, rates of pay, density and pressure."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from knowledge developed from work in ratio and conversion in Year 10.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use formulas involving speed, density, and pressure
Convert between units of rate (e.g. km/h, m/s)
Substitute into formulas and rearrange if necessary""" ;
  curric:id "61"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.643290Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-70
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Loci and construction"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils construct triangles and construct diagrams following specific restrictions using their knowledge of loci and their work on constructions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit follows from vectors where pupils revisited and enhanced their understanding of shape and space. We link that knowledge to this unit as well as building from proof and trigonometry to construct accurate and specific shapes and diagrams.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use compass and straightedge accurately
Understand perpendicular and angle bisectors
Apply basic properties of geometric figures""" ;
  curric:id "70"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.643853Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-53
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Circle theorems"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will use their developed mathematical reasoning skills to derive and use various circle theorems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This is an advanced unit investigating more complex properties of circles, and as such requires in depth knowledge and understanding of shapes, shape properties, proof, angles and ratios.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify parts of a circle (radius, diameter, chord, tangent)
Recognise angle facts in triangles and quadrilaterals
Apply geometric reasoning and proof techniques""" ;
  curric:id "53"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.644386Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra ,
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-43
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Comparisons of numerical summaries of data"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will compare two different data sets and compare different measures of central tendancy when interpreting the data. Pupils will learn to interrogate frequency tables and stem and leaf diagrams both with and without technology."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit benefits from the preceding units on data collection and representations. It furthers pupil understanding of data representation and interrogation.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Calculate mean, median, mode, and range
Interpret and compare sets of data
Understand the purpose of each statistical measure""" ;
  curric:id "43"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.648006Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-statistics .

oakcurric:unit-54
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Plans and elevations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils will be considering a 3-D shape from different viewpoints in order to draw the side and front elevations as well as the plan view."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit follows on from transformations and further develops spatial awareness.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify 2D shapes and 3D solids
Visualise 3D objects from 2D views
Draw front, side, and top elevations""" ;
  curric:id "54"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.656358Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-64
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Functions and proof"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will further develop their understanding of algebraic notation and graphs by learning about functions, their inverses and composite functions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit formalises what a function is, and proof (including strategies to develop a proof). It links with work done on algebraic fractions earlier in the year.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand mappings from inputs to outputs
Use substitution in algebraic expressions
Construct logical chains of reasoning using algebra""" ;
  curric:id "64"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.656906Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-66
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Iteration"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils continue to explore composite functions and develop understanding of iteration, building on their work on functions and proof."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on function notation and compound functions to more efficiently represent and understand repeated applications.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand function machines and input-output
Substitute into simple expressions
Recognise convergence in repeated processes""" ;
  curric:id "66"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.663464Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-46
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Ratio"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to combine ratios, interpret algebraic ratios, and investigate quantity changes and their effect on ratios."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on prior knowledge of simple ratios but deepens understanding by moving into new areas of practical application and generalisation. .""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use language of ratio and proportion
Divide quantities in a given ratio
Scale values up or down using ratios""" ;
  curric:id "46"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.664582Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-56
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Surds"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to recognise surds, handle them in calculations and rationalise fractions with surds as denominators."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to build knowledge around the use of indices, looking deeper at fractional indices and surds in general.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand square and square root notation
Simplify square roots of integers
Multiply and divide simple surds""" ;
  curric:id "56"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.665254Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-65
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Further sequences"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils consider different types of sequences such as Fibonacci and oscillating sequences. They then consolidate their knowledge of different types of sequences by solving contextual problems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds knowledge of all types of sequences covered so far, and links explicitly to theoretical problems and graphical representations.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Generate terms from nth-term expressions
Identify linear, quadratic and geometric sequences
Use recursive rules to build sequences""" ;
  curric:id "65"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.667340Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-45
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Rounding, estimation and bounds"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the impact of upper and lower bounds on additive and multiplicative calculations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds upon ideas around data accuracy and projection that are covered in prior data units this year.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Round whole numbers and decimals appropriately
Estimate answers using compatible numbers
Understand upper and lower bounds in calculations""" ;
  curric:id "45"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.701849Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

