  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672718Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-526-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The suitability of recording data in groups should be considered."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672723Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-781-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A conjecture about a generalisation can be expressed algebraically."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672727Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-781-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The algebraic expression can be used to test the conjecture."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-781-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Substituting values can reveal whether the conjecture is wrong."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672736Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-781-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Substituting values cannot prove the conjecture unless all possibilities are exhausted."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672741Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-715-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The unit circle can help you predict what the graphs of the trigonometric functions will look like"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-715-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The sine and cosine graphs have y values between −1 and 1"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7821-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Desmos is an effective tool for showing the effects of this transformation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7821-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The actual function itself does not need to be known"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672762Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7821-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The graph is stretched by a scale factor of a in the y-direction"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672767Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-632-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The slanted surface of a cone can be cut into congruent triangles."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-632-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """These form a parallelogram with dimensions of the slanted length and half of the circumference of the base."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-632-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The area of the slanted surface can be written as πrl"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-632-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The surface area of the cone is therefore πrl + πr^2"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-632-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The slanted length can be calculated from the height of the cone and radius of the base"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672818Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-637-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The frustum of a cone can be thought of as a cone with the top missing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672823Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-637-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Calculating the surface area for the frustum of a cone is a similar method to finding the area."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672827Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-637-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There is an extra face to consider, the top of the frustum."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672832Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-582-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Equivalent ratios have a scalar multiplier."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672967Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-582-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Two equations can be written which are simultaneous."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-582-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This can be set equal to each other and then solved."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.672979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-466-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The distributive law can be used to find the product of three (or more) binomials."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.673527Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-466-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This can be done by finding the product of two of the binomials first."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.673532Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-466-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The commutative law allows you to choose which two of the binomial expressions to find the product of first."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.673539Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-466-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sometimes your choice can reduce the complexity."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.673544Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-633-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The volume of a cone can be found by displacement."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674449Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-633-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Putting a cone into a cylinder filled with water displaces the water."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674453Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-633-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When the cone is removed, the water level drops."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-633-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The volume of the cone is the difference between the volume of the cylinder and water."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-633-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There is a formula you can use to calculate the volume of a cone."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-807-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If a point on neither line is substituted into the equations, neither equation will be valid"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674471Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-807-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If a point on one of the lines is substituted into the equations, one equation will be valid"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674476Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-807-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Depending on the location of the point, the equation may evaluate to a bigger or smaller value"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674480Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-807-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Replacing the equals sign with an inequality sign would make the statement true"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-707-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The trigonometric ratios for 30° and 60° can be calculated using an equilateral triangle"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-707-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The triangle should have lengths of 2 units"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-707-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By splitting the triangle into two right-angled triangles, you can calculate the ratios"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674499Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-662-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theorem is a statement that can be demonstrated to be true by accepted mathematical operations and arguments"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674506Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-662-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Theorems can be thought of as puzzles to solve, you are showing how to find a result"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674511Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-662-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In order to use this theorem, you may need to draw a diagram or add more information to an existing one"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674516Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-817-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A quadratic equation can be represented graphically"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674521Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-817-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The solutions are where the graph cross the x axis"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674525Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-817-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By studying the graph, you can see where the equation is greater than 0"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674529Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-817-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By studying the graph, you can see where the equation is less than 0"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674534Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-817-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The solution set can be represented algebraically or using set notation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.674538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-607-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Ratios are often used to describe converting between metric and imperial measurements."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675683Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-607-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The ratio is either in the simplest form or in unitary form."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675688Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-607-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """5 miles is roughly 8 kilometers, the approximation is to allow for easy mental calculations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675695Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-643-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The prefix is derived from Ancient Greek."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675700Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-643-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A regular polygon has sides that are all equal and interior (inside) angles that are all equal."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675704Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-643-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An irregular polygon has sides that are not equal or interior (inside) angles that are not equal."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675709Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-679-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The position of a point can be described in terms of another point."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675714Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-679-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When translating, you described moving left/right and up/down."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675718Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-679-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """For bearings, you describe standing on a point and turning a number of degrees to face the new point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675723Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-679-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The bearing is always measured clockwise from North and described with three digits."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-679-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The distance to the new point does not need to be described, but can be."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675732Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-541-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The mean is a measure of central tendency."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675737Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-541-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The mean can only be estimated with a grouped frequency table."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675744Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-541-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Calculating this from a grouped frequency table may be easier when the data is very large."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675749Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-797-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Compound interest can be thought of as a geometric sequence."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675753Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-797-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You can apply your knowledge of geometric sequences to solve compound interest problems."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675758Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-703-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Trigonometric functions are derived from measurements within a unit circle"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675785Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-703-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The right-angled triangle within the unit circle has a hypotenuse of length one unit"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675791Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-703-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The triangle can be scaled to any other right-angled triangle"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675795Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-703-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Similar triangles have the same interior angles"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-703-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Similar triangles have the same trigonometric ratios"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675804Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7681-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Probabilities may appear in unfamiliar contexts"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675854Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7681-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Probabilities may require a strong knowledge of converting between fractions, decimals and percentages"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675859Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7681-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Selecting an appropriate and efficient method for solving the problem comes from evaluating methods"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675863Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7681-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The preferred representation may change depending on the context"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675870Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7824-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your knowledge of identifying transformations of shapes can be applied to graphs"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7824-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This allows you to identify what transformations have taken place"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7824-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Once the transformations have been identified, you can write this in function notation"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.675884Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-648-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If two shapes are congruent, then they are similar."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676632Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-648-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A ratio table can be a helpful tool for checking the multipliers."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676637Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-648-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The multiplicative relationship between the sides of the object is preserved in its image."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-648-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It can be easier to determine (by eye) which shapes are NOT congruent or similar."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676646Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7242-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When problem solving, consider whether any elements are familiar from other areas of maths."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7242-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Keep the goal in mind, it is easy to get distracted by too much information."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676656Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7242-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The size of a sector of a pie chart can be scaled to reflect the population size."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676660Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-665-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theorem is a statement that can be demonstrated to be true by accepted mathematical operations and arguments"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676665Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-665-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Theorems can be thought of as puzzles to solve, you are showing how to find a result"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676669Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-665-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In order to use this theorem, you may need to draw a diagram or add more information to an existing one"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.676674Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-745-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Pressure can be calculated by dividing the force on the objects by the area on which the force acts."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677280Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-745-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The units for force and area determine the units for pressure."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677285Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-745-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By rearranging the formula, you can calculate either force or area."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677289Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-731-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Set notation is a shorter way of writing probability statements"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677294Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-731-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The notation relates to certain aspects of a probability tree"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677298Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-731-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The notation relates to certain aspects of a two-way table"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677303Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-731-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The notation relates to certain aspects of a Venn diagram"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677307Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-731-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The notation relates to certain aspects of a frequency tree"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677312Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-771-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Algebraic manipulation is needed to solve proportion problems."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677316Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-771-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Proportional relationships can be modelled graphically and algebraically."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677321Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-625-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The surface area of a prism is the sum of the area of all the faces."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677904Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-625-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The net of a prism can help find the surface area of a prism but can be time consuming."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677909Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-625-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using known area facts the area of all the faces can be found and summed."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677913Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-625-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is important to find the surface area systematically and efficiently."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677918Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7626-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The surface area of many solids can be calculated by a known method."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677922Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7626-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The volume of many solids can be calculated by a known method."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677927Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7626-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Writing an algebraic statement about surface area/volume can be done from a diagram."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-557-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A box plot requires 5 pieces of information"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-557-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "These are lowest value, lower quartile, median, upper quartile and highest value"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677941Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-557-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Outliers should be included in the range for now"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-557-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "At A level, there are suggested ways to identify outliers and indicate these"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677950Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-721-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are multiple ways to prove the cosine rule"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677954Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-721-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When deriving (or proving) it is sometimes useful to derive other information"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677959Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7684-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Distance travelled is calculated by multiplying speed and time."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677963Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7684-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This is represented on a speed-time graph by the area bound by the graph and the x axis."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677968Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7684-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Calculating this area gives the total distance travelled."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677972Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-759-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The gradient of a curve can be estimated."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677977Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-759-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You can estimate by drawing a straight line between two points on the graph."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677981Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-759-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The closer the points, the more accurate the estimate is."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677988Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-760-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Since the gradient is improved by moving the points closer together, you could consider a point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677993Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-760-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By drawing the tangent to the graph at a given point, you can estimate the gradient at that point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.677997Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-760-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The gradient at that point is estimated by calculating the gradient of the tangent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678002Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-710-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """For packing efficiency, it can be useful to know the length of the longest diagonal"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678009Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-710-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This would be from a bottom corner of a rectangular box, to the opposite top corner"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678014Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-710-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You can construct a right-angled triangle to calculate this"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678018Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-710-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You will need to know the length of the diagonal of the base of the box"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678023Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-710-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There is a formula you can deduce to calculate the longest diagonal"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678027Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-617-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are multiple ways to find the area of compound shapes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678538Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-617-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The most efficient method may depend on the features of the shape."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678542Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-617-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A method is to break the shape into shapes you can find the area of."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678547Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-617-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A method is to complete the shape."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678551Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-617-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A method is to rearrange the shape."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678556Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-626-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A cylinder is not a prism but has a similar structure."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678560Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-626-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The formula for the volume of a cylinder can be derived by using the formula for a prism."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678565Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-626-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This can be used to find the volume of any cylinder."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678570Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-626-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Unknown lengths can be found when the volume of a cylinder is known."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678574Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-730-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Different sample sizes can impact the experimental probabilities"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678579Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-730-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """As the sample size increases, the experimental probabilities approach the theoretical probabilities"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678583Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-730-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A larger sample size is more likely to show a truer estimation of the underlying probability"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678588Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-652-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each length in the shape is multiplied by the scale factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678592Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-652-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each vertex in the object is a given distance from the centre of enlargement."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678597Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-652-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This distance is also multiplied by the scale factor to give the distance of the image's vertex."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678630Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-652-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A positive integer scale factor produces an image that is bigger than the original."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-652-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "To enlarge, you need the centre of enlargement and a scale factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678643Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-752-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You can sketch a graph based on the information you have been given."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678647Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-752-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Important given values should be marked on your sketch."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-752-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """On a distance-time graph, a horizontal line means no distance was travelled for that time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678659Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-752-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A slanted line means that the distance from the start is changing over time."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678666Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-519-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A statistical summary involves the mean, median, mode and range."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678671Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-519-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each summary gives us different insights into a data set."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678675Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-519-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Conclusions may be affected by the way the data was collected."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-831-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When translating, the entire shape moves."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678685Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-831-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Although the point moves, the journey is not drawn."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-831-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A vector can be drawn to show this journey."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678693Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-831-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The vector is a straight line from the start to end point and covers the shortest distance."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678698Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-831-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The top value is the distance left/right, the bottom value is the distance up/down."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678703Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-823-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You can calculate the scale factor from the two volumes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678708Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-823-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Having calculated the scale factor, you can find missing lengths."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678712Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-856-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Desmos is an effective tool for showing the effects of this transformation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678717Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-856-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The actual function itself does not need to be known"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678721Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-856-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The graph is transformed by a reflection in the x axis"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678728Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-854-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Desmos is an effective tool for showing the effects of this transformation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678733Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-854-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The actual function itself does not need to be known"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678738Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-854-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The graph of the function is transformed by a vertical translation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.678766Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7625-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are a variety of approaches to calculations involving shapes."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679541Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7625-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There are many skills you will need, such as algebraic manipulation and geometrical reasoning."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679546Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7625-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Displaced liquids can have their volumes calculated by finding the volume of the solid that displaced the liquid."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679550Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-719-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The formula for the area of any triangle can be used if the lengths of 2 sides are known"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679557Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-719-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The size of the angle between the two sides must also be known"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679562Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-719-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The formula can be used to find a missing side length or angle if the area is known"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679567Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7235-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is important to preserve the relationship between the parts of a ratio."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679571Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7235-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There is a functional relationship between the quantities in a ratio."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679576Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7235-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This relationship can be represented algebraically."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.679581Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-622-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A net is composed of polygons."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680189Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-622-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Folding a net along certain edges and joining others, produces a solid."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680193Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-622-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By studying the polygons in the net, you can deduce what solid is made."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680198Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-622-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By studying the solid, you can draw the net."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-587-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The gradient can be found from two points by considering the change in y over the change in x"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680210Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-587-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The y-intercept can be found using the gradient and one of the points."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680214Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-587-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By substituting the gradient and one coordinate pair into the general equation, you can find the y-intercept."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680221Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-587-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The y-intercept occurs when the x value is zero."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680226Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-587-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is useful to check using the second point while understanding the limitations of this check."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680231Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-847-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The first side can be drawn accurately with a ruler"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680235Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-847-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A pair of compasses should be used to indicate potential positions for the other sides, by drawing arcs"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680240Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-847-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Where the two remaining sides intersect is where the two sides should be drawn to"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680244Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-847-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "All triangles with the same measurements are congruent"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680249Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7819-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your knowledge of loci can be applied to your knowledge of bearings"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680253Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7819-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your knowledge of loci can be used to help solve area problems"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680261Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-756-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Not all real-life graphs can be drawn using sections of different linear graphs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680265Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-756-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The graphs are models, which means that we want them to be useful."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680270Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-756-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Different containers may need different graphs to model filling them."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680275Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-756-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Volume of liquid changes over time and this is affected by container shape."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680279Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-804-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Quadratics can have their solutions estimated using iteration"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680284Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-804-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This can be helpful to quickly determine where the solutions are likely to be"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680291Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-804-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It can be used to check any solutions"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680298Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-547-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Certain data is suitable for a pictogram or bar chart."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680923Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-547-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The shape of the graph can be estimated from the data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680927Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-547-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "For larger data sets, technology can make constructing graphs quicker."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680931Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-560-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A histogram is a bar chart for continuous data"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680936Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-560-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The bars are adjacent due to the nature of the data"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680940Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-560-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The bars are all the same width to allow easier comparisons"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.680945Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-616-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Using fractions, you can calculate the area of a sector of a circle."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682085Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-616-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An exact answer may be given in terms of π"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682090Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-616-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Comparisons can be made between the area and another quantity."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682095Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-628-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are many different types of pyramid."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682099Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-628-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The apex of the pyramid is not necessarily above the centre of the base."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682107Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-628-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Although the base is a polygon, the sides are always triangles."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682111Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-628-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The surface area of a pyramid is the sum of the area of all the faces."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682116Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-641-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Alternate, corresponding and co-interior angles can be identified in diagrams containing pairs of parallel lines."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-641-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Facts about angles in parallel lines can be used to find unknown angles."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682125Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-641-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Facts about angles in parallel lines can be used in succession to find multiple unknown angles."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682130Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7686-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The more trapezia used, the better the estimate."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682183Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7686-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Multiple trapezia can be calculated efficiently."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682187Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7686-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A formula for this can be deduced from the sum of the areas of multiple trapezia."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682194Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-651-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The line of reflection can be vertical/horizontal/diagonal."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682838Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-651-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The line of reflection may go through part of the object."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682845Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-651-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The line of reflection may not touch the object."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682850Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-651-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "To reflect, you need a line to reflect in."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682855Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-585-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Horizontal lines were drawn when finding the solutions of equations graphically."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682859Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-585-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Horizontal lines were drawn because you had a fixed value for y"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682867Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-585-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Vertical lines are drawn when you have fixed value for x"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-585-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Real life problems can be solved using a linear graph."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682890Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-698-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The variable to become the subject may appear in more than one term."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682897Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-698-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is possible the terms cannot be additively combined."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-698-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In this situation, it is possible to factorise with one of the factors being the desired variable."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.682906Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-627-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Drawing the net of a cylinder helps deduce the formula for the surface area."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683596Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-627-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The formula can be used to find the surface area of any cylinder."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683600Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-627-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Unknown lengths can be found when the surface area is known."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683608Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-533-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Interpolation can be used to estimate a value within the data set."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683612Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-533-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Extrapolation can be used to estimate a value outside of the data set."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683619Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-533-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Extrapolation may not be valid as this is outside observed set of data values."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-533-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Interpolation may not be valid due to the limitations of sampling."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683628Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-835-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Vectors can be multiplied by a scalar."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683633Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-835-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Vectors cannot be multiplied by each other."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-835-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Multiplication by a scalar can be done when the vectors are in column form."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-835-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Multiplication by a scalar can be done when the vectors are drawn."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683649Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-822-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An enlargement means the object and image are similar."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683657Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-822-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "All lengths in the object have been multiplied by the scale factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683662Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-822-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using index laws, this means the volume has been multiplied by the scale factor cubed."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683666Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7823-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Desmos is an effective tool for showing the effects of this transformation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683671Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7823-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The actual function itself does not need to be known"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683675Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7823-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The order of transformations is defined by the priority of operations"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.683680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-596-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A table of values can be useful to identify coordinate pairs which satisfy the equation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-596-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By substituting the values for x, you can calculate corresponding values for y."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684206Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-596-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If used correctly, your calculator can be a powerful tool to speed up calculations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684210Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-803-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the value is a solution, then substituting it into the equation should mean the equation evaluates to 0"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684215Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-803-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Since the solution is an approximation, it is unlikely to be exactly 0"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684219Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-803-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By substituting the upper and lower bonds of the estimated value into the equation, you can tell if the estimate is good"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684224Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-803-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the two values produce one positive and one negative value, this implies the graph would cross the x axis"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684228Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-803-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The x intercept would be a solution to the equation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.684233Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-806-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You can use your knowledge of linear graphs to draw the graphs of both equations on the same axes"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685397Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-806-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If there exists a solution, the point of intersection is that solution"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685402Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-806-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the lines are parallel then there are no solutions"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-806-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the lines lie on top of each other, there are infinitely many solutions"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-600-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Inverse proportion graphs are reciprocal graphs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-600-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A table of values can be useful to identify coordinate pairs which satisfy the equation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685420Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-600-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By substituting the values for x, you can calculate corresponding values for y."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685425Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-600-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If used correctly, your calculator can be a powerful tool to speed up calculations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685429Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-825-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By knowing two side lengths and the angle between them in the triangle and image, you can prove congruence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685434Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-825-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The angle between the sides must be the same in both object and image."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685438Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-825-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The given sides must have the same multiplicative relationship."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685445Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-663-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A theorem is a statement that can be demonstrated to be true by accepted mathematical operations and arguments"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-663-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Theorems can be thought of as puzzles to solve, you are showing how to find a result"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685454Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-663-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In order to use this theorem, you may need to draw a diagram or add more information to an existing one"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685461Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-758-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "For straight-line sections of a graph, it is easy to calculate the gradient."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685485Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-758-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The gradient tells us the rate that one quantity changes with respect to the other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-758-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The gradient gives the rate that the $$y$$ variable changes with respect to the $$x$$ variable."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685494Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-758-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The gradient can be interpreted in context and should be for real life contexts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685499Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7757-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your knowledge of the properties of polygons can be applied to vector problems."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685503Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7757-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A regular polygon has a relationship between sides that can be represented with vector notation."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7757-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your knowledge can be used to identify vectors and multiples of known vectors."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685512Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7757-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Through manipulation, you can prove certain properties."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685517Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-839-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Addition and subtraction with vectors follows the algebraic manipulation rules you know."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685522Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-839-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Vectors that are like terms can be collected."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685526Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-839-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The resultant vector can be drawn by sketching."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.685533Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-819-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An enlargement means the object and image are similar."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686129Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-819-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "All lengths in the object have been multiplied by the scale factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686133Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-819-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By the distributive law, this means the perimeter has been multiplied by the scale factor."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686138Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-720-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The sides of a triangle are proportional to the sines of their opposite angles"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686145Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-720-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A diagram can aid with understanding this"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686149Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-720-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The sine rule is useful when you know an angle and side pair and wish to find another pair"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686156Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-720-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "In order to do this, you will need either a side length or an angle"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686161Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-498-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the compound interest rate is fixed but unknown, you can calculate it."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-498-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """To calculate it you need to know the start and end values, as well as the period of time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686805Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-498-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The interest rate is interpreted based on the period of time."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686809Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-498-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The period of time could be per day/week/month/year etc."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-726-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are key differences between frequency trees and probability trees"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686885Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-726-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Frequency trees are constructed using frequencies"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686890Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-726-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Frequency trees display information on how often an outcome happened within a set number of trials"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686895Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7817-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The perpendicular bisector of a line segment divides the line segment into two equal parts"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.686997Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7817-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The perpendicular bisector is the same distance from each end point of the line segment"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687001Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7817-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If you only had the two end points, the perpendicular bisector would still be the same distance from each point"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687006Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7817-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The bisector of an angle divides the angle into two equal parts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687010Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-673-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A solid can be built from its plan and elevations."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687015Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-673-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "All three pieces of information are needed to construct the solid."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687020Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-673-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plan and elevations do not tell you what is going on inside the solid."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687024Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-754-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """In a speed-time graph, a horizontal line means the speed did not change during that time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687029Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-754-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A slanted line means the speed is changing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687033Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-754-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You find this by considering the change in speed with respect to the change in time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687038Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-754-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This is how you find the gradient of the line, which is also the acceleration."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687042Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-754-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A negative gradient means there is deceleration."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687047Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-832-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Vectors are parallel if the gradient of each vector is the same."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687054Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-832-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If drawn, you can see this visually."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687058Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-832-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Parallel vectors are multiples of each other."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687063Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-621-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When problem solving, consider whether any elements are familiar from other areas of maths."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687791Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-621-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Keep the goal in mind, it is easy to get distracted by too much information."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687796Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-621-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """With diagrams, it can be beneficial to add information to them (such as extra lines)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-540-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The median and mode are measures of central tendency."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687805Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-540-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The range is a measure of the spread of the data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687810Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-540-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Calculating these from a grouped frequency table may be easier when the data set is very large."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687814Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-580-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is important to preserve the relationship between the parts of a ratio."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687819Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-580-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Changing this relationship would change the ratio."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687825Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-580-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When the ratio changes, the quantities can be worked out by using equivalent ratios."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687830Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-700-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The sum of the squares of the two shorter sides equals the square of the longest side"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687835Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-700-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The longest side is always opposite the right angle"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687839Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-700-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The difference between the squares of the longest and known shorter sides is the square of the remaining side"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687844Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-700-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A calculator can perform these calculations efficiently"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687848Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-700-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Rounding gives a less accurate answer so there might be times you wish to leave your answer with an operator"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687853Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-520-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Planning involves defining a question to investigate and what data to collect."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687858Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-520-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Collecting involves designing collection methods."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687862Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-520-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Processing and presenting involves calculating statistical measures and graphical representations."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-520-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Interpreting involves reaching conclusions and making inferences."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687873Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-520-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Communicating and evaluating involves identifying weaknesses and improvements."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687878Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-619-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Sometimes you are given a problem with insufficient information to reach a numerical value."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687882Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-619-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Depending on the problem, it may be possible to write more than one equation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.687887Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-619-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is possible these equations can be combined to write a new, more succinct, equation."""@en ;
