  rdfs:label """Depending which variable you chose, you may need to expand a pair of bracketed expressions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.690800Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-484-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your choice may make the substitution significantly easier."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.690805Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7761-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Drawing a diagram can make things clearer."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.690811Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7761-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Adding to an existing diagram can make things clearer."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.690816Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7761-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It can be helpful to start with what you know or can deduce."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.690821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7816-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Constructing a set of points a set distance from a given point produces a circle"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691416Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7816-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A compass should be used for this construction"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691423Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7816-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The point could be the vertex of a shape or contained within a shape"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691428Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7816-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A ruler should be used to indicate two points that are a set distance from a line"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691432Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7816-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The end points of the line should have a compass used to indicate the distance from the point"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691437Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-712-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sometimes an answer may be best left in an exact form"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691441Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-712-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When dealing with right-angled trigonometry, it is important to look at the information you have and can deduce"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691446Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-712-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Consider whether Pythagoras' theorem or trigonometric ratios are more efficient to use"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691450Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7236-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Knowledge of the geometric properties of shapes can be used here."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691455Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7236-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Knowledge of ratio can be used here."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691459Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-545-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The mode is a useful measure of central tendency for certain data sets."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691762Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-545-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The median is a useful measure of central tendency for certain data sets."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691767Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-545-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The mean is a useful measure of central tendency for certain data sets."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691771Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-539-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The mean, median and mode are measures of central tendency."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691775Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-539-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The range is a measure of the spread of the data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691780Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-539-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Calculating these from a frequency table may be easier when there is a larger set of data."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691784Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-844-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A rhombus can be constructed from two congruent isosceles triangles."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691789Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-844-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This can be used to construct a perpendicular to a line through a point."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691793Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-844-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This perpendicular has special properties that can be investigated."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691798Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-844-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The line and point could be part of a shape."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691803Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-659-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A chord splits the circle into two uneven pieces"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691807Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-659-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The smaller piece is the minor segment and the larger is the major segment"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691812Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-659-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using fractions, you can calculate the area of a sector of a circle and you can calculate the curved length of a sector"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691816Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-659-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "To find the perimeter, you will need to add the radius twice"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691821Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-659-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An exact answer may be given in terms of π"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691825Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-527-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Questionnaires are used in a variety of jobs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691857Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-527-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Questionnaires may have been designed to hide intentional bias."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691862Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-527-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When completing a questionnaire, the data it collects should be purposeful."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-575-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A multiplicative relationship is a proportional relationship."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-575-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This multiplier can be thought of as a scaling factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691876Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-575-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The multiplier can be deduced through unitising."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691880Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-575-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Any value divided by itself is equal to one."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691887Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-575-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "One is the multiplicative identity."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-850-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The shorter side can be drawn accurately with a ruler"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691896Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-850-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The perpendicular through the end point of the drawn side should be constructed"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691901Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-850-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The compass should be used to indicate potential positions for the hypotenuse"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691905Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-850-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "All triangles with the same measurements are congruent"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691909Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7689-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The solutions to the quadratic equation can be found using one of your known methods"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691914Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7689-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By sketching the graph, it is easy to define the solution set"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691921Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7689-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "By studying the features of the quadratic, it is easy to define the solution set"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691925Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-579-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """There may be a relationship between quantities A and B and a relationship between quantities B and C"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691930Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-579-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Therefore there is a relationship between A and C"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691935Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-579-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If A : B and B : C then A : B : C and A : C"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691939Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-579-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When the common quantity is not the same in each ratio, equivalent ratios can be used"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691944Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-579-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "For example, if A:B and 2B:5C then 2A:2B:5C and 2A:5C"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691948Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-722-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The cosine rule is useful when you know three sides and an angle are involved"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691956Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-722-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The sine rule is useful when you know two pairs of sides and angles are involved"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691961Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-813-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A solution set can be presented in many different ways"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691968Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-813-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "One of these ways is using set notation"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691973Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-736-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A three event Venn diagram is easier to complete if information from intersecting events is completed first"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691977Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-736-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Venn diagrams may show probabilities, frequencies or outcomes"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691982Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-736-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A three event Venn diagram may have some (or all) events being mutually exclusive"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691986Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-736-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A three event Venn diagram may have events which are subsets of other events"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691991Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-624-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The surface area of a solid is the sum of the area of all the faces."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.691995Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-624-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The net of a cuboid can help find the surface area."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692000Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-624-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The surface area of a cuboid can be found without drawing the net."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692004Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-611-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The formula for the area of a rectangle is bh"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692011Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-611-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The formula for the area of a parallelogram is bh"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692016Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-611-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The formula for the area of a triangle is bh ÷ 2"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692021Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-611-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The formula for the area of a trapezium is ((a+b)h) ÷ 2"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692025Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-735-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An equation can be constructed to find unknown probabilities in tree diagrams"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692100Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-735-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This equation can be manipulated and solved to find unknown probabilities in tree diagrams"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-735-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An equation can be constructed to find unknown probabilities in Venn diagrams"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692109Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-735-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This equation can be manipulated and solved to find unknown probabilities in Venn diagrams"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-678-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Given the real measurements, a suitable scale factor can be chosen."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692406Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-678-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The scale factor should mean the scaled diagram is easy to draw accurately."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692411Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-678-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The scale factor can be determined by the units."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692415Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-678-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The scale factor used should always be clearly written next to the scaled diagram."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692435Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-647-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Problems can be solved using parallel line angle facts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692458Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-647-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Problems can be solved using interior and exterior angles of polygons."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692463Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-647-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Problems can be solved and the solution justified using angle facts."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692467Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-605-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The shape of the graph can be used to identify the form of its equation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692486Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-605-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the graph has a context, then the solutions should be given in context."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.692490Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-815-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Multiple linear inequalities in two variables can be graphed on the same axes"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.693024Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-815-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By testing points in the various equations, you can determine the region that satisfies all the inequalities"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.693029Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-815-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This region is the solution set"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.693038Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-653-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each length in the shape is multiplied by the scale factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694088Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-653-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Each vertex in the object is a given distance from the centre of enlargement."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694092Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-653-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """This distance is also multiplied by the scale factor to give the distance of the image's vertex."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694096Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-653-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A positive fractional scale factor produces an image that is smaller than the original."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694101Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-653-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "To enlarge, you need the centre of enlargement and a scale factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694105Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-672-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The plan is the view from above the solid."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694110Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-672-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The front elevation is the view from the front."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694114Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-672-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The side elevation is the view from the side."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694121Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-672-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "These can be drawn on normal paper."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694128Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-522-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Samples are used when using the whole population would be impractical/destructive."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694133Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-522-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are various sampling methods."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694137Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-522-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A simple random sample is one of the easiest samples to collect."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694141Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-668-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There are many circle theorems so it is important to be clear about each one"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694146Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-668-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Extra lines can be added to a diagram to help determine which theorem to use"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694153Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-668-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Some problems require the use of more than one theorem"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694157Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-542-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There may be cases where one value has more weight (importance)."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694162Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-542-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The weighted mean takes this into account."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-542-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The percent weight given to each value is called a weighting factor."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694173Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-782-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Any algebraic expression must be defined so that it is clear what it represents."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694178Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-782-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Algebraic expressions can be manipulated to create a different form that is equal."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694182Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-782-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This manipulation can be used to prove or show a result."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694187Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-523-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A biased sample is not necessarily bad."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694482Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-523-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You may wish to represent certain groupings in your sample."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694486Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-523-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The sample from each group is proportional to the group size."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694491Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-538-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The mean, median and mode are measures of central tendency."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694495Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-538-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The range is a measure of the spread of the data."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694500Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-538-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Calculating these from a list is easy when the data set is small."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694504Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-636-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The frustum of a cone can be thought of as a cone with the top missing."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694508Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-636-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The volume of a frustum of a cone can be thought of as the difference between two cones' volumes."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694513Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-636-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This formula can be manipulated to rely on information from the frustum only."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.694517Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-504-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Every positive integer can be broken down into prime factors."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706154Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-504-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Every positive integer can be written as a product of its prime factors."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706159Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-504-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Prime factor products can be simplified by using index notation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706163Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-791-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is possible to generate the sequence and therefore show whether a value appears in the sequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706168Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-791-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is possible to use your knowledge of multiples to reason whether a value appears in a given sequence."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706172Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7189-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Quadratic equations can model real-life situations."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706179Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7189-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Solutions would need to be interpreted in context."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706186Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7189-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The difference of two squares is not only used in algebra, but can be used to quickly calculate numerical expressions."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706191Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-7189-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Where there is a choice of method, you will decide the most efficient method to use."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706196Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-20337-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Addition of negative integers can be made easier by considering zero pairs."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706856Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-20337-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Subtractions can all be re-written as additions of the additive inverse."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706860Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-20337-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The rules for multiplying with negative numbers can be extended to division."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.706865Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-571-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Rounding and estimation are practical maths skills."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708066Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-571-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "They can be used to quickly estimate the cost of a project."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708070Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-571-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Sometimes you will need to apply common sense to rounding in context."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708075Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-492-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When calculating percentage profit or loss, you are interested in the change."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708338Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-492-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the final amount is more than the original, there is profit."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708343Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-492-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If the final amount is less than the original, there is loss."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708348Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-492-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "This change can be described as a percentage of the original amount."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708352Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-492-5
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A negative percentage is interpreted as a loss."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708357Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-480-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Additively combining the equations does not eliminate one variable unless the coefficients are the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708361Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-480-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Equivalent equations should be formed so the coefficients of one variable are the same (if not already)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708370Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-480-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When considering the coefficients, use your knowledge of LCM to help."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708375Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-769-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Inverse proportion equations are of the form y = k ÷ x^n"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708380Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-769-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The equation can be written in the form yx^n = k"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708385Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-769-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "k is the constant of proportionality."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708389Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-769-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "To find k, you can use a pair of values."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.708393Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-461-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An expression can be described as being factorised."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.712979Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-461-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """An expression is fully factorised if the highest common factor has been taken out."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.712984Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-461-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The distributive law can help us factorise an expression."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.712991Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-717-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Reading solutions from trigonometric graphs is the same as reading solutions from any other graph"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714578Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-717-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Due to the period, there may be more than one solution"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714582Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-717-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """It is possible to predict the number of solutions that exist within a given range"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714586Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-693-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An algebraic fraction can have more than one term in the denominator."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714676Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-693-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Your equivalent fraction knowledge can be used to simplify the fraction."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714681Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-697-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is important to identify which variable is to become the subject."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714685Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-697-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Like terms containing the new subject should be collected."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714690Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-697-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "You should be prepared to utilise any of your algebraic manipulation skills."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.714694Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-570-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When considering safety contexts, you want to be able to guarantee safety limitations (weight of materials)."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717534Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-570-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "When considering costs, you may wish to know the maximum cost to you."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717542Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-570-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """When training in sport, you may wish to know the time you need to beat in order to win a race."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717547Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-476-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "If you have one value, you can use a linear graph to find its pair."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717641Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-476-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The pair of values will satisfy the linear equation."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717645Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-476-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """If the x and y variables have context, then their values can be interpreted within that context."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717649Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-476-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "With quadratic graphs, there may be more than one value to find."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717654Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-794-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "A quadratic sequence does not have a common difference."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717658Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-794-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The second differences between terms are equal."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717663Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-794-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The general n^th term formula is an^2 + bn + c"@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.717667Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-568-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The biggest possible sum comes from adding the upper bounds."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719197Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-568-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The smallest possible sum comes from adding the lower bounds."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719201Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-568-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The biggest possible difference comes from subtracting a lower bound from an upper bound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719205Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-568-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The smallest possible difference comes from subtracting an upper bound from a lower bound."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719209Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-773-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "There is a shorthand for writing a function."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719620Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-773-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The notation means that the whole function does not need to be written out each time."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719624Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-773-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The notation should always be defined at the start."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719629Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-773-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "It is possible to substitute the notation for the function it represents."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719633Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-762-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the gradient of the radius through a given point, you can find the equation of the tangent at this same point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719638Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-762-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You have already proved that the tangent at any point on a circle is perpendicular to the radius at that point."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719642Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-762-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """You have already proved that the product of the gradients of two perpendicular lines is -1"""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719646Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-762-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using the gradient of the tangent and the coordinates of the point, you can find the equation of the tangent."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719651Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-465-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The distributive law can be used to find the product of two binomials."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719680Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-465-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "An area model can be used to explore the underlying structure."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719685Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-465-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Both of the terms in one bracket must be multiplied by both terms in the second."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719689Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-677-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Maps are a practical example of a multiplicative relationships."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719892Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-677-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The scale factor is the multiplier."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719896Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-677-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "The multiplicative relationship can be written as a ratio."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719903Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-677-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Real-life scaling involves writing a ratio involving the parts which are dependent on each other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.719908Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-515-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """The commutative law allows the product of two numbers represented in standard form to be easily calculated."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720615Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-515-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Using your knowledge of the index laws, you can combine powers with the same base."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720620Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-515-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Standard form calculations can be done using a calculator."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720626Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-578-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Bar models, ratio tables and double number lines can help with ratios."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720846Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-578-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Real-life scaling involves writing a ratio involving the parts which are dependent on each other."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720853Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-578-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """A recipe is an example as to scale the recipe up or down requires keeping the proportions of the ingredients the same."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720857Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-499-1
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """By considering the calculations for compound interest, you can be more efficient."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720862Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-499-2
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Through understanding the structure, you can adapt to changing percentages."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720866Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-499-3
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label """Part of that structure is understanding the period of time for each interest rate."""@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720871Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

oakcurric:keylearningpoint-lesson-499-4
  a curric:KeyLearningPoint ;
  rdfs:label "Part of that structure is understanding finding a percentage of a percentage."@en ;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:21.720875Z"^^xsd:dateTime .

